lobbying_activities.description:
Action on the development of the 2010 Department of the Interior, Environment, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, including specific provisions relating to the US Geological Survey funding for water management and climate research, the USDA Forest Service Forest Health Protection program, invasive species research and development, Land and Water Conservation Fund projects, Willamette Valley and Camp Creek Army Corps of Engineer Projects, Forest Legacy projects, Forest Service wildland fire funding, the Cooperative Endangered Species Fund, the Albemarle/Pamlico National Estuary Program, funding for river restoration projects, the National Landscape Conservation System budget, the Healthy Lands Initiative budget, US Fish and Wildlife Service international programs, US Forest Service international programs, the Multi-Species Conservation Fund, Peru/US Free Trade Agreement logging annex, appropriations related to Nestucca, Pacific Northwest Streams, and Hells Canyon acquisition, and Savannah River Comp. Water Resources Study; The fiscal year 2010 National Defense Authorization Act, including specific provisions relating to Sikes Act agreements, the Department of Defense Legacy grant proposal, Department of Defense readiness and environmental protection initiative, authority of combatant commanders to fund conservation activities overseas, military base expansion, training and testing area requirements, authority to participate in conservation banking programs, and provisions related to the impact of climate change on national security;  the 2010 Department of Homeland Security Appropriations Act, including specific provisions relating to border security initiatives;  the 2010 Department of Defense Appropriations Act, including specific provisions relating to funding for the Department of Defense Legacy grant program, the Readiness and Environmental Protection Initiative, overseas conservation activities, and other military activities impacting biodiversity;  the 2010 Agriculture, Rural Development, Food and Drug Administration, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, including specific provisions relating to funding for the Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service Plant Protection, primarily Emerging Plant Pests line, and funding for invasive species, pests and pathogens;  the 2010 Commerce, Justice, Science, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, including specific provisions relating to NOAA funding, Coastal and Estuarine Land Conservation Program, Fisheries Habitat Restoration programs, Pacific Coastal Salmon Recovery Fund, and coral reef conservation programs;  H.R. 2764, Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2008, including specific provisions relating to foreign operations, international conservation funding initiative, and coral triangle funding; FY10 Energy and Water Development Appropriations Act, including specific provisions relating to Army Corps of Engineers ecosystem restoration projects;  H.R. 1, The American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009, including specific provisions relating to funding for BLM and Forest Service wildland fire management account, funding for the US Army Corps of Engineers, natural resource restoration, coastal habitat restoration and noxious weed control;  FY2010 Presidents Budget, specifically support for Land and Water Conservation Fund, Forest Legacy, and wildland fire funding;  FY10 appropriations packages; and proposed legislation to establish permanent appropriations for ocean research, conservation, and restoration.

Covered officials contacted:  Director for Environmental Readiness and Safety, Office of the Deputy Under Secretary of Defense, Department of Defense;  Assistant Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Environmental, Safety, and Occupational Health, Department of Defense; Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Navy, United States Navy; Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Army for Environment, Safety, and Occupational Healthy, United States Army; Deputy Director, Joint Guam Program Office, United States Navy; Director, Bureau of Land Management; Budget Director, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Department of Commerce;
Chief Financial Officer, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Department of Commerce;  Director, Office of Ocean and Coastal Resource Management; National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Department of Commerce;  Manager, Coral Program, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Department of Commerce;  Associate Director Land and Water Ecosystems, Council on Environmental Quality;  Associate Director for Policy Outreach, Council on Environmental Quality; Chair,  Council on Environmental Quality;  Acting Assistant Secretary for Policy, Management, and Budget, Department of the Interior;  Program Examiners, Office of Management and Budget;  Associate Director, Natural Resources, Energy, and Science, Office of Management and Budget;  Program Examiner, Commerce Branch, Office of Management and Budget;  Branch Chief, Commerce Branch, Office of Management and Budget; and Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service Administrator, US Department of Agriculture.

Action on the development of the upcoming Homeland Security Authorization Act, including specific provisions relating to the Department of Homeland Security waiver authority, authority for a border buffer program, issues relating to the U.S./Mexico Border Fence, consultation requirements for border security infrastructure, and the monitoring and mitigation program for ecological impacts of border security infrastructure; and discussion drafts on Healthy Borderlands Act of 2008 and Border Conservation and Security Act.  

Covered officials contacted:  Deputy Executive Director, Security Border Initiative, Department of Homeland Security;
Chief of Staff, Customs and Border Protection, Department of Homeland Security;  Associate Director for Habitat, US Fish and Wildlife Service;  National Borderlands Coordinator, Department of the Interior;  Deputy Secretary, Department of the Interior; Assistant Secretary, Department of Defense; and Deputy Director, Bureau of Land Management.

HR 3081 - foreign operations appropriations for fiscal year 2010 and amendments related to Exim Bank; 
Discuss various proposals related to the application of privacy laws in the context of Asian Pacific Economic Cooperation;
Educate trade representatives on the issue of cross-border market access.

HR 627 "Credit Cardholders Bill of Rights Act" and S 414 "Credit CARD Act" - address concerns and educate Members of Congress on credit card pricing and marketing practices; 

Educate Administration and Congress on industry response to crisis in mortgage lending, including loan modification; HR 1456 "Consumer Overdraft Protection Fair Practices Act" - address concerns and educate Members of Congress on proposed legislation that would affect overdraft protection programs; 

HR 1728 "Mortgage Reform and Anti-Predatory Lending Act" - address concerns and educate Members of Congress on proposed legislation affecting the underwriting of residential mortgages;

HR 2695 "Credit Card Fair Fee Act" - educate on the role of interchange in the electronic payments network;

Offered technical advice on transition from the Federal Family Education Loan Program to direct lending.

S 272 "Derivatives Trading Integrity Act" and HR 977 "Derivatives Markets Transparency and Accountability Act" - educate Members of Congress regarding the value of derivatives; 

Discuss proposals for comprehensive regulatory reform of market regulation to address recent market turmoil; HR 2861 and S 1074 "Shareholder Bill of Rights Act" - educate Members of Congress on the impact of proposed changes to corporate governance practices; 

As a major lender to Detroit auto makers, keep the Administration and Congress informed on the status of negotiations over their debt obligations;

Discuss the use of public private partnership for green infrastructure development.

HR 1083 "Business Activity Tax Simplification Act" - support creation of physical presence standard under which a state may tax the income of business;  

Educate Members on the impact of proposals to require additional information reporting on fund transfers to foreign accounts; HR 1944 - support extending the active finance exception to Subpart F of the Internal Revenue Code, which requires current taxation on income earned overseas;

Educate Members of Congress on the competitive impact of proposals that affect our ability to defer US taxation of overseas income until the income is repatriated.

